# Adversary fixture: FM6-b — language tag in lowercase (@en) — canonical form
# Hypothesis: This is the canonical BCP47 form.  All compliant parsers must
#   accept it and produce "Hello"@en as the literal.  Paired with FM6-a to
#   expose equality divergence when one parser normalises and the other does not.
# Expected outcome: accept-with-1-fact
outcome: accept
fact-count: 1
object-lang-tag: en
divergence-hypothesis: ObjectMismatch vs FM6-a when parsers disagree on normalisation
spec-ref: W3C RDF 1.1 N-Triples §2.4; W3C BCP47
